30/10/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The chief of the BiH armed forces' joint staff, Lieutenant General Sifet Podzic, announced on Saturday (October 28th) that a commission that selects professional army soldiers began operating earlier in the week. 
The panel also is in charge of appointing civil servants at the BiH Defence Ministry and the armed forces. 
Successful applicants would sign two-year contracts, subject to extension. 
(Dnevni avaz, RTRS - 29/10/06)
